main event: On April 25, 1966, over 200 objects were observed flying in a 'V' formation in the sky over Baltimore, Maryland.
interesting points: The objects were seen at an altitude of approximately 500 feet and moved at a slow speed with no visible exhaust., The sighting involved multiple witnesses, though the exact number was not specified., A bright greenish-white fireball was also reported by a tower controller at Friendship Airport on the same date., The objects did not make contact with the control tower, raising questions about their identification., The report mentions that there was no physical evidence found for the sighting.
sighted object: over 200 unidentified flying objects in a 'V' formation
witness description: The report primarily cites observations but lacks specific witness identification.
